# simulated data
rng = default_rng()
x = rng.normal(size = 100)  
y = rng.normal(size = 100) 
Data = pd.DataFrame({'x':x, 'y':y})
Data['xSign'] = (Data.x > 0 )

Contour Plot¶

In [12]:
x = np.linspace(-np.pi, np.pi, 50)
y = x

X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)

Z = np.cos(Y) / (1 + X**2)

p = plt.contour(X, Y, Z, levels = 10)
plt.clabel(p)
plt.show()
Out[12]:
<a list of 14 text.Text objects>

geom_boxplot()¶

use + coord_flip() to switch between vertical and horizontal boxplots

In [20]:
AutoNew = Auto.loc[:,['mpg','cylinders']]
AutoNew['cylinders'] = Auto['cylinders'].astype('category')
ggplot(AutoNew, aes('cylinders', 'mpg')) + geom_boxplot(fill = 'red')

ggplot(AutoNew, aes('cylinders', 'mpg')) + geom_boxplot(fill = 'red') + coord_flip()
